[[ファイル:Oshima Shrine's Third Torii Gate.jpg|サムネイル|右|Third torii, with the evergreen oak grove beyond]]

'''Ōmiya Shrine''' (おおみやじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Ōshima, Tokyo|Q1204507|WD=Q1204507|1=Ōshima, Tokyo}} ({{ill|lt=Izu Ōshima|Q1070580|WD=Q1070580|1=Izu Ōshima}}), {{ill|lt=Tokyo|Q1490|WD=Q1490|1=Tokyo}}.

It is identified with '''Ajiko Shrine''' (あじこじんじゃ), a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}}<ref name="geo">[https://izuoshima-geo.org/know/highlights/culturalsite/bunkasite-12.html 大宮神社] - 伊豆大島ジオパーク</ref>.

=== Overview ===
Its founding is unknown. It was originally enshrined in the Ajiko settlement in the southern mountains, but to avoid repeated volcanic ashfall from eruptions it was moved to the current site in the Muromachi period ({{ill|lt=1466|Q6559|WD=Q6559|1=1466}}), and at that time {{ill|lt=Amaterasu|Q455602|WD=Q455602|lt=Amaterasu-ōmikami|1=Amaterasu}} was additionally enshrined<ref name="geo"/><ref name="navi">[https://oshima-navi.com/shrine/shrine003.html 大宮神社] - 伊豆大島ナビ</ref>.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* {{ill|lt=Amaterasu|Q455602|WD=Q455602|lt=Amaterasu-ōmikami|1=Amaterasu}}
* Ajiko-no-Mikoto - eldest child between {{ill|WD=Q8009611|lt=Kotoshironushi|Q8009611|WD=Q8009611|1=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto}} (Mishima Daimyōjin) and one of his consorts, Habuhime-no-Mikoto ("Habu no Ōkisaki," enshrined at {{ill|lt=Habuhime Shrine|Q134930157|WD=Q134930157|1=Habuhime-no-Mikoto Shrine}}). Younger brother: Haji-no-Mikoto (enshrined at {{ill|lt=Hajikama Shrine|Q134930376|WD=Q134930376|1=Hajikama Shrine}}).

=== Cultural properties ===
* Twelve-seat {{ill|lt=kagura|Q1348260|WD=Q1348260|1=Kagura}} of Nomashi Ōmiya Shrine - town-designated folk cultural property<ref name="geo"/>.
* Evergreen {{ill|lt=shii oak|Q11540757|WD=Q11540757|1=Japanese ship Shii}} grove of Nomashi Ōmiya - Tokyo-designated natural monument<ref name="geo"/><ref name="navi"/>.

